description.narrative: Despite delays due to Covid19 restrictions, progress was made with supporting capacity building of partners. These included introducing the National Human Rights Institution of Malaysia (SUHAKAM) and it’s Office of the Children’s Commissioner (OCC) to child friendly practices, supporting probation pilot scale-up, ;supporting launch of the National Action Plan on Anti-Trafficking in Persons 2021-2025 (NAPTIP 3.0) and community-based child protection initiatives for children affected by migration. Additionally, evidence generation initiatives progressed though mapping of social service workforce for children and research on impact of Covid19 on children’s mental health and on street children in Sabah. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:03/02/2022
